---
name: Update ARCHITECTURE.md on Infrastructure Changes
globs:
  - prisma/schema.prisma
  - src/routes/**/*.js
  - src/services/**/*.js
  - src/worker*.js
  - src/server.js
  - src/config.js
  - railway.json
  - package.json
  - .env.example
alwaysApply: false
---

When you modify any file matched by this rule, you MUST:

1. Update docs/ARCHITECTURE/ARCHITECTURE.md:
   - prisma/schema.prisma changed → update the Database Models section
   - src/routes/*.js changed → update the API Endpoints section
   - src/services/*.js changed → update the External APIs section
   - src/worker*.js changed → update the Pipeline & Worker Flows section
   - src/server.js or src/config.js changed → update the Summary section
   - package.json changed → update the Service/Resource Table
   - railway.json or .env.example changed → update Environment Variables
   - Always update the "Last updated" date at the bottom
   - Never remove existing content, only add or edit

2. After updating ARCHITECTURE.md, immediately run in the terminal:
   ./scripts/sync-docs.sh "brief description of what changed"

3. Tell me: "✅ ARCHITECTURE.md updated and pushed to GitHub — [what changed]"
